The port of PLplot to wxWindows was made by adding two files:
wxwin.cpp (the device driver) and wxPlot.cpp (the wxWindows interface
class). The device driver does the main work: drawing lines,
polygons,... via wxDC class functions. Because only a PLStream
structure is passed to the device driver by the internal PLplot
functions, a pointer to the wxDC class is included in the PLStream
structure in plstrm.h.

The main changes for the device driver were:
wxwin.cpp:
	all device dependant functions have to be added here
drivers.h:
	adding the declarations for the device driver	
plcore.h:
	adding the device dependant functions to the dispatch table
plDevs.h:
	undefining all device drivers except the wxwin one

The wxPlot class is derived from plstream.cc. 
wxPlot.cpp,
wxPlot.h:
	added the constructor
	wxPlot::wxPlot(wxDC *dc, int w, int h)
	and renaming plstream to wxPlot.

other changes necessary to be able to compile the code:
plConfig.h:
	set some macro definitions.
plplot.h:
	comment out Alloc2dGrid and Free2dGrid so that a call to 
	Alloc2dGrid does not reference itself.	
plargs.cpp, 
plstripc.cpp:
	comment out 
	char *strdup();
